## Fix: Knowledge Graph Explorer blocked on PUBLISHED/IN-REVIEW domains

### Context
The Explorer's primary query endpoint (`POST /dtwin/sync/filter`) was being
blocked by `PermissionMiddleware` when a domain was in PUBLISHED or IN-REVIEW
status. The middleware listed the entire `/dtwin/sync/` path prefix in
`_STATUS_GATE_EDIT_PATHS`, which treated all POSTs under that prefix as
mutating operations — including the read-only filter queries powering the
Explorer graph search and expand phases.

The CSS layer (`permissions.css`) already correctly excluded `data-page="digitaltwin"`
from read-only form-disable rules, so the UI remained interactive, but every
Explorer query silently returned 403 server-side.

### Changes

1. `src/shared/fastapi/main.py`
   - Replaced the broad `/dtwin/sync/` prefix in `_STATUS_GATE_EDIT_PATHS`
     with the two specific mutating endpoints: `/dtwin/sync/start` and
     `/dtwin/sync/load`.
   - Added an explanatory comment clarifying that read-only POSTs such as
     `/dtwin/sync/filter` must stay accessible on non-DRAFT versions.

### Modified files
- `src/shared/fastapi/main.py`

### Test results
- 2704 unit tests passed, 57 skipped
- 1 pre-existing failure (pyshacl not installed locally, unrelated)
- e2e and property test suites skipped (environment dependencies missing)

